Date: 07-10-2025 & 14-10-2025

Aim
To write a given input string to a file named output.txt.
To read the file contents back into the program.
To count uppercase and lowercase letters and print their counts.
Algorithm
Read a line of text from the user.
Write the text to a file named output.txt.
Read the content back from output.txt.
Initialize upper=0, lower=0.
For each character, increment upper/lower counters appropriately.
Print upper on first line and lower on second line.
End program.
Program (Java)
import java.util.*;
import java.nio.file.*;
public class CaseCountFileIO {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        String s = sc.nextLine();
        Path p = Paths.get("output.txt");
        Files.write(p, s.getBytes());
        String content = Files.readString(p);
        int upper = 0, lower = 0;
        for (char ch : content.toCharArray()){
            if (Character.isUpperCase(ch)) upper++;
            else if (Character.isLowerCase(ch)) lower++;
        }
        System.out.println(upper);
        System.out.println(lower);
        sc.close();
    }
}


Sample Output
3
8
Result
Successfully persisted and retrieved string via file I/O.
Accurately counted uppercase and lowercase letters.
